summary: As a student at Wageningen University I was involved with a number of projects that provided experience in laboratorium work and field research, as well as academic consultancy training with actual stakeholders. I was able to utilize that training during my thesis and internship. My thesis concerned the effects of a pesticide and an invasive parasite on honeybee populations. My internship was held at Agresearch in New Zealand, concerning the effectiveness of the biological control of an invasive beetle using an introduced predator. Here I increased my practical experience in biological control and farmer-researcher relations. After graduation I was employed to make field observations of bats and swallows on behalf of an ecological consultancy firm. For the immediate future I would like to increase my experience further and apply my broad education to a good cause. My mobile number is 0611234171.
